<html><head><title>Weekly Community News 8/15</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Weekly Community News 8/15</h3><p>Greetings fellow Norathians! Allan here reporting on the latest news and updates for you on our EverQuest servers.   I'll be bringing you this report every Sunday, so if you have any server news <a href="mailto:element1586@aol.com">e-mail it all to me!</a><br><blockquote><br><b>Morell-Thule:</b><br>-New guild "New Lagacy" took down took down Fennin Ro on their first attempt last Tuesday. We would like to Congratulate them on there accomplishment.<br> <br>-Open Raid on Sunday August 15th at 4pm CET is 10am EST and 7am PST. Target is Rallos Zek, and the raid calls for levels 62+. Any of those who are interested in joining, should be in PoT at the scheduled time in front of the zone where the raid will happen.<br> <br>-Upcoming raid in Sol Ro. All players must be flagged for Bertox to enter Solusek Ro's Tower. Targets for this raid are: Bert and Zeks. Any questions contact Niphreedil.<br><br><br><b>Torvonnilous:</b><br>-"Dingo" Australian based guild is now recruiting. Raid times are Weds-Sunday 6:30pm - 11:30pm AEST. 4:30am - 9:30am EST. For more information visit <a href="http://www.dingoguild.com/">http://www.dingoguild.com/</a><br> <br><br><b>Firiona Vie:</b><br>-August 15th at 10AM EST "League of Honour" will be going into Plane of Fear for parts of epic.  Contact the guild for further information.<br> <br>-"Rising Darkness" formally known as "Nightwind" works their way into Planes of Time! Two EP gods were taken down, and there are 2 more to go. They are now recruiting. Guild site <a href="www..nightwindguild.com">www..nightwindguild.com</a> Check it out if interested.<br><br><br><b>Antonius-Bayle:</b><br>-(D`Pikeys) Recruiting. Normal raiding times are between 6.00pm GMT and 12 Midnight GMT. They often raid about 4-5 times a week for 3-6 hours per night. For more information visit <a href="http://www.thepikeys.iogaming.com/">http://www.thepikeys.iogaming.com/</a><br> <br><br><b>Bertoxxulous:</b><br>-Friday August 20th "Lost Boys" will be raiding PoS, Tactics and Epic Pieces.<br> <br>-Saturday August 21st A small guild alliance will be going to Plane of Fear to get some epic drops  Contact Ogdan for information.<br> <br><br><b>Innoruuk:</b><br>-"GRG" is an Elemental guild, "At the moment were looking to bolster our ranks, and are opening the door to ALL classes for recruitment." Interested please visit <a href="www.grg.cc">www.grg.cc </a><br> <br>-"Notabilis Kruoris" is a guild that prides itself on the loyalty of its members. If you desire to commit yourself to a family and aren't afraid to take on mobs with unzerg like numbers and unconventional methods, then you may want to consider "Notabilis Kruoris". Visit there message boards at <a href="http://p202.ezboard.com/bteamnotoriouskillers">http://p202.ezboard.com/bteamnotoriouskillers</a>.<br> <br>-"Formidable" is recruiting. All classes except Shadow Knight and Shaman. They are an Elemental Planes enabled guild, and that is where they spend most of our time. They are two kills away from Time and will be there soon. Interested? Contact them at <a href="www.formeq.net">www.formeq.net</a><br> <br>-"Tired of EQ not really being about fun anymore? Tired of people looking out for only themselves? Well, in (Valomni Todom), we have fun and look out for each other before ourselves." If Valomni Tdoms's motto is appealing to you, stop by their website <a href="www.vt-eq.com">www.vt-eq.com</a> and check them out. "Post an application and join the family."<br> <br>-"The Knights of Shadowthorne" are recruiting. They want people that are committed to playing and being part of the team. Visit <a href="www.shadowthorne.dns4me.com">www.shadowthorne.dns4me.com</a>. There you will find more information about their guild.<br> <br>-"Everlasting Dragon Lords" looking for recruits. If you are interested /join EDLrecruit in game, or /who all "Everlasting Dragon Lords" to group up or chat with their members for information. "We're looking for some good natured, fun loving, good humored people that know their class!"<br> <br><br><b>Xev:</b><br>-"Stormwind" is recruiting. If you are interested in a fun family EP level guild that strives not to zerg, check them out at <a href="www.stormwindguild.net/recruiting.php">www.stormwindguild.net/recruiting.php</a>.<br> <br>-"Depraved Indifference" is currently looking for the following classes: Necromancer, Wizard, Cleric, Enchanter, and Monk. Visit their site at <a href="http://depravedindifference.guildwizard.com">depravedindifference.guildwizard.com</a><br> <br>-"Social Anomaly" is now recruiting. We would like to congratulate them on taking down the Avatar of War with 21 people. They are a growing raid guild, raid either 8pm EST on weekdays or 4pm EST on weekends with smaller raids any other time. They are currently working on VT keys - emp keys - and ST keys-. Talk to Donoven or any officer/member in-game or send an email to socialanomaly@hotmail.com.. Can also check out Social Anomaly at <a href="www.socialanomaly.com">www.socialanomaly.com</a><br></blockquote><br>Remember if you have anything to send in please do submit and we'll get it posted!</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Sunday, 15 August, 2004<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=671">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=671</a><br>Printed On: Thu Mar 16 6:17:41 PST 2006<br>©2005 IGN Entertainment</font></span>